tldr: The user requested to implement a database, an admin dashboard, and
  authentication for a sleep questionnaire application based on a Statement of
  Work. The project involved updating demographics, setting up a PostgreSQL
  database with Prisma, creating API routes for responses and CSV export, and
  building a simple admin dashboard with middleware-based authentication.
overview: The user aimed to enhance a sleep questionnaire application by adding
  persistent data storage and a client-facing admin dashboard. The approach
  involved updating the application's data model to capture detailed
  questionnaire responses and demographics, then integrating a PostgreSQL
  database (NeonDB) via Prisma. Key decisions included denormalizing demographic
  data for easier CSV export and opting for a simplified, middleware-based
  authentication system for the admin dashboard. The implementation covered
  creating new API endpoints for data submission and retrieval, building a login
  page, and a dashboard to view and export responses. The outcome is a fully
  functional data storage and access system, ready for deployment, with clear
  instructions for database setup and testing.
